definitions.explanation_en: A proper noun, typically used as a feminine given name in English-speaking countries, derived from the French name 'Tracy', which itself originated from a place name in Normandy, France.
definitions.explanation_cn: 一个专有名词，通常用作英语国家女性的名，源自法语名字 'Tracy'，而该名字最初来源于法国诺曼底地区的一个地名。
definitions.example_en: Tracy is the project manager who led the team to success.
definitions.example_cn: 特蕾西是带领团队取得成功的项目经理。
